Former West Ham and Watford boss Gianfranco Zola is in the frame to take charge at his former club Cagliari, according to reports in Italy.

La Gazzetta dello Sport have suggested that the 48-year-old is favourite for the job with the Serie A strugglers and could be appointed during the two-week winter break.

Zeman was sacked as Cagliari manager on Tuesday morning. A statement on the club's website read: 'Cagliari Calcio announces that from now Zdenek Zeman leaves the technical guidance of the first team.

